The paper focuses on predicting the top young researchers who will achieve the highest citation increment in a given time period. This involves analyzing various factors that can drive an author to be fast-rising, such as research topics, venues, and temporal features. These factors are all relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including deep learning (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), machine learning (cs.LG), and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
